The Stockholm Convention on Persistent Organic Pollutants (Annex B, Part II, paragraphs 1–5) allows for temporary use of DDT for the purpose of malaria-vector control while maintaining the goal of reducing and ultimately eliminating the use of DDT, and calls for the development of alternatives.
